Updated Specific Objectives (The "Research" part)
To include this data logging, your objectives should look like this:
Analyze the visibility gap for informal workers in Cameroon.
Design a mobile-first platform with a centralized logging system to capture user search queries and worker availability.
Develop the platform using a stack that supports real-time data storage (like Firebase or PostgreSQL).
Evaluate how the captured data can be used to predict market trends and inform local economic policies.
The "Socio-Economic" Hook
This feature allows you to argue that your platform doesn't just help one worker; it helps the whole community by identifying what services are missing. For example, if many people search for "electrician" in a specific neighborhood but find no results, the government or NGOs can use your data to justify opening a vocational training center there.
For your technical architecture, I recommend looking at Google Firebase Analytics or Mixpanel to see how to log these events without slowing down the mobile experience.
