New "Housing" Theme for your Literature Review
You should now add a section on Informal Real Estate Markets in Sub-Saharan Africa:
The Problem: High "Agency Fees" and the risk of scams when using roadside agents (demarcheurs).
The Impact: Review how digital transparency reduces "transaction costs." When a student in Yaoundé can see a room in a specific "quarter" online, they save days of physical searching and transportation costs.
Source: Look at the Centre for Affordable Housing Finance in Africa (CAHF) for reports on Cameroon's housing market challenges.
Technical Advantage: Scalability & The "Super-App" Model
Since you mentioned scalability and designing from scratch, you are essentially building a localized "Super-App" (similar to WeChat or Gojek).
Bilingual Search: In your methodology, you’ll need to explain how you handle Natural Language Processing (NLP) or simple keyword mapping for "French/English/Pidgin" (e.g., searching for "Chambre" vs. "Room").
The WhatsApp Bridge: This remains your "killer feature." By keeping the final transaction (scheduling the visit) on WhatsApp, you avoid the complexity of building an in-app chat, which keeps the app lightweight and high-performance on older phones.
Socio-Economic "Search Log" Use Case
Imagine your data logs show: "90% of searches in Bonamoussadi are for 'Studio rooms under 50,000 CFA', but 0 results were found."
Actionable Insight: This data is gold for real estate developers or the Ministry of Housing (MINHDU) to understand where the actual demand is versus what is being built.
